items.content:
Hi Jessica, to investigate further, can you request the below from the advertiser?


1) Screen shot of conversion value mapping from Appsflyer

2) Screen shot of the events postback setup in Appsflyer

3) Screen shot of SKAN events reporting dashboard in Appsflyer to see the tiktok attributed events are reported by Appsflyer


Also, if they haven't already, I would recommend that they complete the following:

  • Update your Mobile Measurement Partner SDK. Updating to the SKAN-supported version of the MMP SDK will ensure that your  app is registered for SKAN-based attribution and gives you the ability to optimize and measure installs and post-install events from iOS 14 users. 
  • Complete the Conversion event configuration in their MMP interface.This ensures that ad networks like TikTok can receive post-install events and event values from SKAN API in order to provide optimization and measurement for iOS 14 campaigns. 
  • Send all events to TikTok via your MMP. In order to help improve performance of your app campaigns, we recommend sending TikTok all data - including unattributed data - from your MMP.
IDk why the screenshots didnt attach lol but here they are:

Here is what the client sent back:


Find below the information requested:

About discrepancies between platform and AF, are you referring only to iOS? For us it is pretty normal to see a % of discrepancies between the MMP and the SAN's partners dashboard. 

1) Screenshot of conversion value mapping from Appsflyer

Are you referring to SKAN Conversion Studio right? We added two events: complete registration and start trial.


2) Screenshot of the events postback setup in Appsflyer

For iOS

For Android 

3) Screen shot of SKAN events reporting dashboard in Appsflyer to see the tiktok attributed events are reported by Appsflyer

Until now we're not seeing in-app events for any of our active iOS campaigns. With tiktok we're already seeing a good volume of installs every day so I think it is matter of time for the events to start appearing on the dash. Even though please confirm me If you see any missing information.


Also, if you haven't already, I would recommend that you complete the following:

    • Update your Mobile Measurement Partner SDK. Updating to the SKAN-supported version of the MMP SDK will ensure that your app is registered for SKAN-based attribution and gives you the ability to optimize and measure installs and post-install events from iOS 14 users. 
      Is there any chance on my side to confirm the AF SDK version? What version should be using? 
    • Complete the Conversion event configuration in their MMP interface. This ensures that ad networks like TikTok can receive post-install events and event values from SKAN API in order to provide optimization and measurement for iOS 14 campaigns. 
      I think this is already done, right?
    • Send all events to TikTok via your MMP. In order to help improve performance of your app campaigns, we recommend sending TikTok all data - including unattributed data - from your MMP.  
      Done since the beginning (screenshots)

Hope this information is what you expected. If not, please just let me know!

Hey Jessica, thanks for passing that along; I find it odd that we're seeing SKAN conversions on the ad group/campaign level, but no conversions are reported in their Events Manager:




I escalated this to TPS and you can view the progress on that ticket here.
Yes and no iOS installs too?! So weird - thank you so much!

do you know the answer to these: 

  • Update your Mobile Measurement Partner SDK. Updating to the SKAN-supported version of the MMP SDK will ensure that your app is registered for SKAN-based attribution and gives you the ability to optimize and measure installs and post-install events from iOS 14 users. 
    Is there any chance on my side to confirm the AF SDK version? What version should be using? 
  • Complete the Conversion event configuration in their MMP interface. This ensures that ad networks like TikTok can receive post-install events and event values from SKAN API in order to provide optimization and measurement for iOS 14 campaigns. 
    I think this is already done, right?


or should i ask this on the other ticket?


I was about to email the client and ask for the new screenshots 


thank you!

Hey Jessica, following up with updates from the TPS ticket:


The screenshots shared are from the correct places, but they are cropped and do not show the full picture. 


The first one with SKAN Overview (below), that section is only showing installation, but missing the other events that SKAN reported.


For the event Mapping, there are two of them, but I cannot tell which one is from SAN (SRN) and from Legacy integration. 


Also for the Conversion Value mapping, cannot tell if that was taken from SAN (SRN) or the legacy module.


Can you please ask the client to zoom out and/or maybe try to find a way to take a full screenshot of the events that they have concerns with?


Regarding their two follow-up questions, I'll pass those along to TPS to answer with certainty. Thanks!
Thank you! I'll let you know as soon as they respond with the new screenshots.

Find here all the details:


1. As I mentioned, we saw the first in-app events just now

 so that's why I have not included on the previous email. 


2. About both events mapping: one is for Android and the other for iOS. This is the first integration we made for the Zumba App so we made it under the SRN only. Legacy was not integrated at all. 


3. Conversion Value Mapping is for any integration, it is made in a separate tab. It is not made for SRN or Legacy separately but for all partners.

From Dagmawe in the TPS ticket:


I checked our tables and I do not see MMP SDK version logged on our side. 

I think the client should have access to that or they can ask the MMP:

https://support.appsflyer.com/hc/en-us/articles/207032126-SDK-integration-overview


An overview of steps needed to enable SKAN interoperation between AppsFlyer <> TikTok can be found here.

"About the SDK version (i'm confirming this with my Tech team) but we have v6.12.2 so according to the article, should we upgrade to 6.2.3?



Regarding SKAN Setup the answer is yes the measurement mode is active and the events are already integrated in 'active integration partners' (screenshot on this same thread)"

Hi Joey,


I was preparing SKAN training for the TSC team and came across your ticket.

For SKAN metrics, it will not be shown in Result as you can hover your mouse over the column, and it will be shown only in Conversions (SKAN).

Clients are advised to check the metrics in (SKAN) column. 


Does this address the issue? I was being confused why we now start talking about SDKs :S

Thanks for stepping in here Chan, that explains a lot! So is it expected behavior for SKAN metrics to come up as 0 across the board (screenshot 1 below), and these instead will be reported under Measurement Partner as the data source (screenshot 2 below)?

Appreciate the help here.

SKAN metrics should show in your screenshot 1. MMP metrics will show in screenshot 2. These metrics are different.

For the Events Manager screen, internal employees have restrictions on data access to the US user data, and I am presuming it might be the cause. The best step to verify is to ask the client whether they can see the metrics as the SKAN metrics should be visible to the client.

https://bytedance.larkoffice.com/docs/doccnPVRxTuy9cNoeSihYRkny1b


(I dont think the client ever asked about metrics on Events Manager, so maybe it is safe to ignore for now. )


On the other hand, this client has not configured anything on SKAN Conversion values, meaning that they will not be able to see any in-app events except for installs, as Dagmawe pointed out earlier.

Here are the steps on how to:

https://support.appsflyer.com/hc/en-us/articles/4403727223185-SKAN-Conversion-Studio

Thanks again, Chan! How were you able to audit whether or not the client has configured anything for SKAN Conversion values? I requested access from Ray for the first link you sent, so haven't had a chance to view anything there at the moment.

Hi Joey, I will show you how in the training tomorrow. Basically, we have a tool to view the client configs.


Just to be sure, the link I provided is regarding our restricted access on client metrics on TTEM, and the 'conversion values' that I am referring to is about the configurations.
Hey Joey! Any update here? Are they good to go now? Thank you!!

Hey Jessica, we're seeing conversions on the ad group-level under the Conversions (SKAN) column, and it's confirmed that we're recording events including app installs. It's still showing up as 0 for me, but this may be due to restricted data access internally (the client will see the source of truth in their dashboard). Can you confirm with them that they're seeing non-zero numbers in their view?
Hey Joey - Zumba confirmed they are seeing SKAN events (non-zero) on their side for the iOS app campaign!
Awesome news! Do they have any other concerns?
